    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1955-12-29T14:33:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1955-12-29T14:33:00-05:00" n="471"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d471">
                <head>471. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Department of State</gloss> to the
                        <gloss type="to">Embassy in Israel</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d471fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 784A.56/12–2955. Confidential. Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_BDC1"
                            >Bergus</persName> and approved by <persName corresp="#p_RFH1"
                            >Russell</persName>, who signed for <persName>Dulles</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,<date calendar="gregorian" when="1955-12-29T14:33:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 29, 1955—2:33 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>445. Please convey to <gloss target="#t_FonMin1">FonMin</gloss> text following
                    message from Secretary: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“Dear Mr. Minister: I received your letter of December 12 just as I was
                            departing for Paris. With regard to request of the Israel Government for
                            purchase of arms in this country, which you mention, Mr.<persName
                                corresp="#p_AGV1">Allen</persName> informed Ambassador <persName
                                corresp="#p_EA1">Eban</persName> on December 13<note n="2"
                                xml:id="d471fn2">See <ref target="#d454">Document 454</ref>.</note>
                            that we were unable reach decision this time for number of reasons,
                            prominent among them being recent incident on Syrian border.</p>
                        <p>“In your letter you also give Israel Government’s views with respect to
                            some of questions involved in an Arab-Israel settlement. I hope the
                            Israel Government will continue to give its most careful consideration
                            to solution at this time of the various issues between Israel and her
                            Arab neighbors. I am convinced that a resolution of this conflict would
                            be of the greatest benefit to Israel and go far to remove a threat that
                            otherwise must be of the gravest concern to all who are interested in
                            its welfare.</p>
                        <p>“With kindest personal regards, sincerely yours,<persName
                                corresp="#p_DJF1">John Foster Dulles</persName>.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Signed original enroute Tel Aviv by pouch.<note n="3" xml:id="d471fn3">
                        <persName>Dulles</persName> signed this message on December 23.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="strong">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
